This paper discusses the stability of bipedal robots during walking/running motion, which is a common topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves designing a motion limit cycle and a motion stabilizer, which are both related to control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of new technologies and the advancement of knowledge, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the natural movement of humans, which could be related to machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV).
